{"lemma":"حَرْبٌ","slug":"حَرْبٌ","root":"ح.ر.ب","root_slug":"ح-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَرْب","root":"حرب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7533"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be enraged, to be furious, to be angry"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"war","tags":["countable","uncountable"],"examples":[{"text":"تَتْرُكُ ٱلْحُرُوبُ أَثَرًا طَوِيلَ ٱلْأَمَدِ عَلَى ٱلْمُجْتَمَعَاتِ ٱلْمُتَضَرِّرَةِ.","english":"Wars leave a long-lasting impact on affected communities."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"warfare","tags":["countable","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَرِبَ (ḥariba) (form I)","tags":["countable","form-of","noun-from-verb","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rage","tags":["countable","uncountable"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *x̣arb-. Cognate with Biblical Hebrew חֶרֶב (ḥɛ́rɛḇ, “sword”).\n\nFrom Proto-Semitic *x̣arb-. Feminine because it meant a tool in Proto-Semitic, namely a blade."},"ipa":["/ħa.ri.ba/","/ħarb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7533","headword_ar":"حَرْبٌ","root":"Hrb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"War, battle, fight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conflict;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silomN","text_ar":"سِلْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) consisting, first, in"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shooting arrows, one at another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"then, in"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thrusting, one at another, with spears;"},{"kind":"text","text":"then, in"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"combating one another with swords;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and then, in"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grappling and struggling together:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Suh, TA:) it is [generally] fem.; (S, L Msb;) but its dim. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HurayobN","text_ar":"حُرَيْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kh, S, L, Msb,) contr. to rule, (L, Msb,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*urayoEN","text_ar":"ذُرَيْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quwayosN","text_ar":"قُوَيْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furayosN","text_ar":"فُرَيْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a fem. sense, (L,) because originally an inf. n. [of which the verb ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haraba","text_ar":"حَرَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":") seems not to have been used as meaning “ he waged, or contended in, war ”], (El-Mázinee, S,) or in order that it may not be confounded with the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobapN","text_ar":"حَرْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) Seer makes its origin to be the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobN","text_ar":"حَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which, however, is originally an inf. n.: (L:) sometimes it is masc.; (IAar, Mbr, S, Msb, K;) but this is extr.: (L:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuruwbN","text_ar":"حُرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaEato bayonahumo HarobN","text_ar":"وَقَعَتْ بَيْنَهُمْ حَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"War happened between them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAmati AlHarobu EalaY saAqK","text_ar":"قَامَتِ الحَرْبُ عَلَى سَاقٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"battle, became vehement, so that safety from destruction was difficult of attainment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And making it masc., as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qitaAlN","text_ar":"قِتَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobN $adiydN","text_ar":"حَرْبٌ شَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A vehement fight"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"battle."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu HarobK","text_ar":"اِبْنُ حَرْبٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A warrior:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnY","text_ar":"بنى"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu AlHarobi","text_ar":"اِبْنُ الحَرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the warrior;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he who suffices for war, and who defends."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb in that art.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAru AlHarobi","text_ar":"دَارُ الحَرْبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"countries, of the unbelievers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those called by the Muslims"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the polytheists,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between whom and the Muslims there is not peace."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K.) In the saying of Aboo- Haneefeh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAnato mak~apu A_i*o *`Aka HarobFA","text_ar":"كَانَتْ مَكَّةُ اـِذْ ذٰاكَ حَرْبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", the meaning is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAra HarobK","text_ar":"دَارَ حَرْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mekkeh was at that time a place of which the people were at war with the Muslims"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.)       -A2-  It is also an epithet; originally an inf. n. (L.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN HarobN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ حَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaribN","text_ar":"حَرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but it is] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadolN","text_ar":"عَدْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man vehement in war, and courageous;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHorabN","text_ar":"مِحْرَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHoraAbN","text_ar":"مِحْرَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHorabN","text_ar":"مِحْرَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man of wars;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man of war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHoraAbN","text_ar":"مِحْرَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a known, experienced warrior."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Being originally an inf. n.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobN","text_ar":"حَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an epithet is used in the same form as masc. and fem. and sing. and pl.: (K:) so that one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN HarobN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ حَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobN","text_ar":"حَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN miHorabapN","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ مِحْرَبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An enemy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) whether, or not, actually at war. (K.) So in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA HarobN limano","text_ar":"اَنَا حَرْبٌ لِمَنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaArabanaYi","text_ar":"حَارَبَنَىِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am an enemy to him who wars with me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is an enemy to me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Harobu fulaAnK","text_ar":"حَرْبُ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the enemy of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Some hold that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobN","text_ar":"حَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. [or rather a quasi-pl. n.] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAribN","text_ar":"حَارِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHaAribN","text_ar":"مُحَارِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Suh","TA","Kh","S","L","Msb","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}